    overview: `• Public ATM and self-service banking technology company (NYSE: NATL)\n• Formed from the Oct 2023 split of NCR Corporation into NCR Atleos (ATMs/banking) and NCR Voyix (retail/restaurants)\n• Headquartered in Atlanta, GA\n• CEO Tim Oliver\n• ~10,000+ employees; operates/manages ~650,000+ ATMs globally\n• Revenue ~$4.4B\n• The world's largest ATM network operator — manages the entire ATM lifecycle from manufacturing to software to services`,
    products: `• ATM hardware manufacturing and sales\n• ATM software (operating system, transaction processing, security)\n• ATM managed services (monitoring, maintenance, cash management)\n• Self-service banking kiosks\n• Allpoint network: The largest surcharge-free ATM network (~55,000 ATMs in US)\n• Customers buy because: Banks need ATMs and someone to manage them. The shift to ATM-as-a-service means banks outsource the entire ATM operation`,
