    overview: `• Public specialty materials and contamination control company for semiconductor manufacturing (Nasdaq: ENTG)\n• Founded 1966 in Billerica, MA\n• CEO Bertrand Loy\n• ~8,000+ employees\n• Revenue ~$3.4B (post-CMC acquisition)\n• Provides advanced materials, specialty chemicals, and contamination control solutions used in every step of semiconductor fabrication\n• Completed acquisition of CMC Materials in Jul 2022 for $6.5B — added CMP (chemical mechanical planarization) slurries and pads`,
